author: news.com.au
title: Millions in deals sealed at coffee fair
text:
EXPOESPECIALES Cafe de Colombia 2015, considered one of the largest coffee industry fairs in Latin America and the Caribbean, has resulted in deals worth about $US7.2 million ($A9.92 million), the Colombian National Coffee Growers Federation, or FNC, says.
THE fair, organised by the FNC and government export, investment, tourism and national brand promotion agency ProColombia, exceeded expectations, FNC general manager Roberto Velez Vallejo said in a statement.
